Hi Discord Managers! 👋🏼

Hope everyone is doing well! I’ll be covering Carlos’s responsibilities as the Network Architect this upcoming week. 🌟 Opportunity Alert:
If any of you are interested in stepping up to become a permanent Network Architect co-lead alongside Carlos, please DM me your CV or LinkedIn profile by the end of the week. Dr.Sanchez and me will be reviewing applications and selecting co-head(s) to assist Carlos.

Dr. Sanchez has agreed to recognize each of our Network Architects on a special LinkedIn post this week as a sincere thank you for your outstanding leadership and continuous commitment to our community! 🏅 We’re also continuing discussions with MIT on additional ways to recognize and celebrate your impactful contributions, and MIT is enthusiastically supporting these efforts. Let’s maintain our momentum—I’m excited to collaborate with all of you! 💪🏼🔥

Oscar Sanchez

🚀 Hello Discord Managers Team! 🚀

I hope you're all energized after today's productive session! Here's what you need to know to kick off our Discord optimization mock-week effectively:

🛠 This Week's Objective:

You'll begin working on your selected Discord optimization. Important: You're not required to fully complete your optimization this week. Instead, we'll start the process, dedicating focused 30-minute work sessions each day.

🔍 Available Optimizations (Choose One):

Sesh-Bot — Schedule Events 📅

Natural language commands (!create) for event scheduling

Automatic timezone conversions and attendee tracking

Sesh-Bot — RSVP Management ✅

Reaction-based RSVPs

Auto-DMs with local event times

Real-time attendee counter and easy editing

Sesh-Bot — Google Calendar Sync 🔄

Immediate two-way synchronization via Google API

No manual exports; seamless integration

Note: Additional optimizations and details from Dr. Sanchez (write-up/video) are coming soon!

Date/Time: Tomorrow, 12:00 PM ET ⏰

Action: Please keep track of any questions or blockers during the process, so we can efficiently address them.

Form groups of 3–4 managers per optimization.

2–3 members: Builders and implementers 🧑‍💻

1 member: Scribe/documenter 📖 (responsible for detailed recording of progress and outcomes to share with Community Coordinators)

📌 Communication Hub:

Keep all coordination, updates, and resource sharing exclusively in the <#1353449809075503145> channel.
